    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Park at St. Jean]]></title>
    <link href="http://playdegex.github.io/2010/09/park-at-st-jean/"/>
    <updated>2010-09-24T20:56:42+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://playdegex.github.io/2010/09/park-at-st-jean</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TJZkFlPeIJI/AAAAAAAAzXM/xNHxk1et6Sg/s1600/DSCN2518+%28Modified%29.JPG" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="190" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TJZkFlPeIJI/AAAAAAAAzXM/xNHxk1et6Sg/s320/DSCN2518+%28Modified%29.JPG" width="320" /></a></div>


<p>St. Jean de Gonville has a really tranquil park of trees and shrubs. Aswell as the swings in the middle there are some good&nbsp;rockeries&nbsp;and hiding places to play on and in.<br /><br />The ground floor of the climbing &nbsp;frame is great, it has a table and chairs for a child scale picnic.<br /><br />St. Jean park is a great venue for a lazy afternoon.</p>
]]></content>
